<title>UK: Oxford Molecular to take stake in Cambridge.</title>
<headline>Oxford Molecular to take stake in Cambridge.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-02-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>Britain's Oxford Molecular Group Plc said it would make an initial cash investment of 0.5 million stg in drug research firm Cambridge Combinatorial.</p>
<p>Oxford would take a stake of 20 percent in the issued ordinary share capital of Cambridge.</p>
<p>Cambridge Combinatorial would also have to offer three further tranches of deferred shares, equivalent to 0.5 million stg, to Oxford Molecular.</p>
<p>Oxford Molecular said the investment was a strategic move to providing a range of integrated drug design services to its pharmaceutical services.</p>
